This paper is about improving machine translation using a convolutional neural network, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as neural networks, which are commonly used in the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses an attention mechanism, which is a common technique in neural machine translation, falling under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision, falling under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
